This paper deals with transfer learning between two classification tasks, which is a common problem in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also uses neural networks and adversarial training, which are common techniques in deep learning and ML, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper deals with document classification, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the paper uses embeddings, which are a common technique in NLP and ML, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another possible category.
